        <abstract> 
<p>Regrets he cannot come to hear DS’s paper ["On the structure of Mont Blanc", <hi rend="italic">Q. J. Geol. Soc. Lond.</hi> 11 (1855): 11–27]. Has a lively interest in the subject.</p>  
<p>Edward Forbes has misrepresented his view on foliation and cleavage [<hi rend="italic">Athenæum</hi> 30 Sept 1854].</p> 
            <p>CD is convinced DS’s view will replace Huttonian and Lyellian view of metamorphic schists.</p> 
<p>Recommends H. C. Sorby’s paper [probably "On the origin of slaty cleavage", <hi rend="italic">Edinburgh New Philos. J.</hi> 55 (1853): 137–50].</p> 
        </abstract>
